comment: Dr. Carver remains one of my favorite professors at CMU. If you have a chance to take one of her higher-level courses, I also highly recommend!

Prof. very interested in the subject and a reasonable guy. Has very high expectations. His courses are hard, but you learn a lot from them. His courses are not for wimps or those with weak quantitative skills.

He's approachable and willing to help the top students land internships. He is tough but fair. Don't try to screw around with him.

This guy has THE most screwed up grading system EVER. He's a great guy on a personal level, but he's a horrible teacher. The whole course is set up for you to fail. You can spend days working on the homework and not get anything correct. In class, he does really simple examples, but the homework and tests are crazy-hard. Avoid at all costs!
Absolutely fantastic
Best professor in Heinz

Lassman's cases cover a wide scope of management, leadership and ethics. Class discussion was by far the best out of any discussion based class I have experienced.  Favorite class: Bill Cowher-suprise speaker. Insight in Cowher's leadership style is invalualble. I'm fortunate and lucky to have had such a great experience.

Professor Lassman is awesome. His class is a lot of fun -- it's largely case discussion-based, and he is great at leading the discussion and providing valuable insight from his extensive experience. I am so glad I got to take this class with him - I learned a lot, and had a great time doing it!
Good book, bad and boring lecture

He's very knowledgeable, but his teaching could be better. Lectures can seem a bit of a drag and during office hours, he sometimes answer with ''read the textbook''. The course material and labs are amazing though.

comment: He might look like a stuff old man when you first meet him, but he's actually incredibly knowledgeable and interesting, and just when you think you've had all the assembly you can take, he cracks a joke under his breath and suddenly it's all good again.
If you have the opportunity to take 213 with Bryant and O'Hallaron, I strongly recommend you do so.

She doesn't show up, she doesn't give her time to her students, but she really is a lovely woman.
She's clearly the most knowledgeable of all the MT teachers. If you're looking for the best private instructor, she's obviously the best choice.

Such a great teacher, made Elementary French a fun class (but not a super easy pass). Was actually really interested in getting us to learn French, and was overall a great teacher with a fun personality. Heavy workload with a textbook, workbook, and classwork, so be prepared for that.
Bonnie is wonderful and engaging! She is also very personable and kind. Hers was my favorite class.

She makes learning French Culture at 9.30 am very engaging. She's over the top in a fun way, and she's very much an awesome professor but do not get into her bad books. That being said, just make sure you do her work and participate in class because attendance and participation make up a significant portion  of the grade. Highly recommended!
good teacher and real nice! Fun in class.

She gets a lot of her own problems involved in class and makes the class atmosphere extremely depressing. comment: Mean and angry all the time, she made me and other students cry.  I learned editing alright and using cameras but I also hate myself because of how mean she was.

Susie values hard work, so don't take her classes if you're coasting. In my experience, she bonded more obviously with certain students and picked on the weakest link in the class, so don't be that person. If you need help with software, hardware, editing, or finding artists whose work may be of interest to you, she is a wealth of information.

Suzie is definitely tough and she might throw some devastating blows to your ego, but she knows her material. If you work hard (especially outside of class), not only will you learn a damn lot, but she might even like you. And trust me, she is a great professor to have on your side.

Everyone else seems to like him, but I don't see the appeal. He didn't return ANY of our papers w/ feedback/ grades until the final grades had already been posted. Literally no feedback until the it was too late to matter. Not to mention his lectures were pretty dull.

comment: This class is so easy LOL. There is so much work though. He is also really passionate about the topics which he talks about, which makes it less boring than a usual English class.

comment: He's passionate.

Tim Dawson was an excellent interp professor. He has a real passion for the topics he teaches in class. Some of the assignments were tedious and quite dumb. Tim also has quite a bit of assignments, so watch out.

In class, Dawson does a really great job of analyzing opinionated pieces of writing without taking a side himself. As far as writing goes, Dawson will not hesitate to point out flaws, but he offers constructive feedback that helps you write a better paper.

Dawson is very interested in the subject he teaches and is very intelligent. He asks interesting questions.  He requires lots of work, but work you do actually helps later with huge assignments.  Sometimes he can be a little misleading, but if you ask questions, he answers them!

He's an English teacher, so you'd expect him to be very clear, concise, and perspicacious, all of which are true. His instructions in class may be a bit unorthodox at times, but his knowledge of the world, clarity, and eclectic style make his class quite enjoyable.
took the intro B&W with him.  Super awesome prof.  Funny, fun, and informative. He can go a bit slow some times, but its nice if you've never done any work in the photo lab.
Great prof!  Really allows you to explore photography with open eyes when your first getting into it.  Its a wonderful class wonderful experience.

It was unbelievable to see such a positive vibe in the classroom, thanks to her. You can clearly see her enthusiasm and excitement of all the material. She is so interested in everything and takes time to get to know you. Would 11/10 recommend.
She is very passionate with her lectures, that makes interesting and entertainment.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Amazing lectures

comment: Really passionate, really engages you with each building

Diane Shaw inspired me continuously throughout my architectural education @ Carnegie Mellon. By far my favorite processor throughout my college experience. She has a way of making buildings come to life in a rich, passionate, funny way & challenged us to view architecture as a story. I took every class of hers that I could :)

Professor Shaw is an absolutely astounding professor, easily my favorite one from my six years at Carnegie Mellon.  I took every architecture class of hers that I could, and loved them all.  She makes it about more than just what's in the textbook: you learn about culture, the other arts, and history as well.  So much admiration for her!

Really funny, and really interested in what she teaches--and by virtue of that, makes it interesting to learn. Was only mildly curious about architectural history before I took the class, but the class turned out really interesting and even kind of fun. Don't miss a lecture if it can be helped.

I've taken 3 drawing classes from Cooper and saw tremendous improvement in not only mine, but everyone else's work. However great a professor he is, he is NOT an easy A at all. He's super critical of drawings and knows what he's talking about. Super talented.
He is probably one of the most interesting professors you will ever have. He tends to tell a lot of stories that seem pointless but they alway have a meaning...plus he is a great drawing teacher!
The best professor in architecture ever.

Doug Cooper is so pro. You'll learn a lot from him, as long as you're willing to work hard and improve yourself. You don't have to be a good drawer to do well in his class; he appreciates your effort, and always loves improvement. Don't fall too behind on portfolios, because they coincide with Studio deadlines all the time.
Best professor in Carnegie Mellon's school of architecture, hands down.

I don't know if I've ever had such a dedicated instructor.  She put tremendous effort into the class, was extremely helpful and encouraging, and is highly intelligent.  I'd definitely take another class from her.
A really, really excellent teacher - one of my best at CMU. If you work with him and take all the opportunities for extra work that he gives, you'll certainly do wonderfully.

Burak is a great professor. Lectures are clear and he gives plenty of practice for exam. He also teaches you to use Matlab for more than plotting, and it's the first core course that does so. However, he could do better at providing outside help, as office hours are very limited.
Dr. Oz is a great teacher and his lectures are very useful.

kai is the best kept secret of second year and you should take all of his history classes. don't be fooled by the art-vs-kai attitude of the 2nd year. kai seems a lot more rigid compared to art but to understand where he's coming from you really need to take his history course.  definitely one of the best profs in cmu arch, worth your tuition.

Extremely well read and invested in giving students a strong foundation and understanding of the material being covered.  Always willing to offer extra help, even if inconvenient.  Basically, you get what you put in with Kai-you'll love him if you're a hard worker and will find him less appealing if you aren't.
Good course. Lots of great material.

He is such a funny guy, always telling jokes right in the middle of lecture.  It's a tough class but he tries to keep it interesting.  The good thing is he is always trying to help and is quite approachable.  It's not easy, but don't be afraid to ask him for help.  He is very understanding!
has a great accent, always willing to help, doesn't give bad grades unless you're a jerk

HANDS DOWN ONE OF THE BEST PROFESSORS I HAVE EVER HAD AND AN AMAZING PERSON. she had an incredible impact on me the one summer i spent learning from her. she is the reason i chose to pursue architecture.  knows how to put fun in the studio and connect with the students. i wish that she could remain a mentor in my life forever!!!
